Nigerian Army said its troops have arrested a wanted Boko Haram suspect, Bubayi Isa, from Panama village, Gunda District, Biu Local Government Area of Borno State following a tip off. Texas Chukwu, spokesperson for the Army said in a statement that further investigation revealed that Bubayi is suspect No 37 on the list of wanted Boko Haram terrorists published by the Nigerian Army Headquarters. He added that other suspects arrested alongside Isa are Muhammad Buba & Abdullahi Abubakar from the same area while Yakubu Abdullahi hails from Sabon Gari Gado also in BornoState â€œThe suspects were arrested in Kalaa village in Hong LGA of Adamawa State. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.